  "texts": [
    "Hanlin 18: This approach denotes the best overall result of the 17 participating teams in the VQA-Med 2019 task.",
    "Considering the VQA-Med 2019 dataset shares an official test split, we directly borrow the results reported in the public leaderboards (https://www.aicrowd.com/challenges/ imageclef-2019-vqa-med/leaderboards).",
    "MEVF-BAN 10: This approach introduces a framework that combines an unsupervised denoising auto-encoder with supervised Meta-Learning to quickly adapt to the VQA problem in scenarios with limited labeled data.",
    "We utilize the results of MEVF-BAN on various VQA benchmarks as reported by PMC-CLIP 13, where MEVF-BAN is finetuned on each specific dataset and evaluated on the corresponding official test set.",
    "CPRD-BAN 11: This approach proposes a two-stage pre-training framework that focuses on learning transferable features from radiology images and distilling a compact visual feature extractor tailored for Med-VQA tasks."
  ],
